...causing all kinds of trouble.

521
00:52:08,412 --> 00:52:10,346
Finally hit the big time.

522
00:52:11,749 --> 00:52:15,048
IKilled three people in a holdup.

523
00:52:15,252 --> 00:52:17,379
One of them a pregnant woman.

524
00:52:19,890 --> 00:52:21,881
Bad news all around.

525
00:52:36,306 --> 00:52:37,568
It's a tumor, Paul.

526
00:52:39,243 --> 00:52:40,972
A brain tumor.

527
00:52:42,713 --> 00:52:43,873
They got...

528
00:52:44,715 --> 00:52:46,808
...x-ray pictures of it.

529
00:52:48,218 --> 00:52:50,743
It's the size of a lemon, they said.

530
00:52:53,457 --> 00:52:54,719
And...

531
00:52:55,893 --> 00:52:57,417
...way down...

532
00:52:59,263 --> 00:53:01,458
...deep inside,
where they can't operate.

533
00:53:03,500 --> 00:53:05,161
I haven't told her.

534
00:53:06,937 --> 00:53:08,905
I can't think how.

535
00:53:12,676 --> 00:53:14,803
For the life of me, Paul...

536
00:53:16,313 --> 00:53:19,305
...I can't think how to
tell my wife...

537
00:53:22,786 --> 00:53:24,754
...she's going to die.

538
00:54:49,406 --> 00:54:51,499
Oh, oh, God.

539
00:54:52,175 --> 00:54:53,733
Oh, God.

540
00:54:57,614 --> 00:54:59,013
I'm going.

541
00:54:59,216 --> 00:55:00,148
What?

542
00:55:00,350 --> 00:55:03,217
To see Dr. Bishop. I'm going.

543
00:55:03,553 --> 00:55:05,020
Today.

544
00:55:05,522 --> 00:55:08,252
Soon as we get that new inmate
squared away.

545
00:55:08,625 --> 00:55:09,819
That bad?

546
00:55:10,527 --> 00:55:11,960
Oh, yeah.

547
00:55:34,051 --> 00:55:36,246
The boy's doped to the gills.

548
00:55:39,222 --> 00:55:40,450
Hand me them clothes.

549
00:55:43,493 --> 00:55:45,393
William Wharton?

550
00:55:47,164 --> 00:55:49,029
You put on these clothes now.

551
00:55:57,140 --> 00:55:58,266
We'll have to do this.

552
00:56:00,477 --> 00:56:02,104
Hellraiser, huh?

553
00:56:02,312 --> 00:56:04,974
Look more like a limp noodle to me.

554
00:56:08,752 --> 00:56:12,552
You've been declared competent, son.
You know what that means?

555
00:56:13,290 --> 00:56:14,985
You're gonna ride the lightning.

556
00:56:18,095 --> 00:56:19,722
Shut up, give us a hand.

557
00:56:20,597 --> 00:56:22,292
Hellraiser.

558
00:56:53,263 --> 00:56:54,753
You don't look so good.

559
00:56:56,733 --> 00:56:58,701
Look like you're running you a fever.

560
00:57:04,474 --> 00:57:06,066
Boss Edgecomb?

561
00:57:07,577 --> 00:57:09,511
I needs to see you down here.

562
00:57:12,082 --> 00:57:14,380
I got things to tend to, John Coffey.

563
00:57:17,054 --> 00:57:20,421
You just stay still in your cell.

564
00:57:32,002 --> 00:57:33,230
E Block.

565
00:58:09,473 --> 00:58:10,963
Come on, let's go.

566
00:58:12,209 --> 00:58:14,302
Come on. Look alive, big boy.

567
00:58:28,992 --> 00:58:30,220
Careful.

568
00:58:33,730 --> 00:58:34,628
Careful.

569
00:58:34,831 --> 00:58:35,661
Step up.

570
00:58:35,966 --> 00:58:36,898
Step up.

571
00:59:17,607 --> 00:59:18,938
Ain't this a party now?

572
00:59:19,376 --> 00:59:20,468
-Is it or what?
-Let him go.

573
00:59:20,677 --> 00:59:22,304
-Shoot him.
-See who you hit.

574
00:59:22,512 --> 00:59:23,979
Shoot the son of a bitch.

575
00:59:24,281 --> 00:59:25,111
Shoot him!

576
00:59:25,348 --> 00:59:27,976
Hit him, Percy!
Goddamn it! Hit him.

577
00:59:28,185 --> 00:59:29,652
Hit me, you limp noodle.

578
00:59:29,853 --> 00:59:30,751
Hit him, Percy!

579
00:59:30,954 --> 00:59:32,148
Goddamn it, hit him!

580
00:59:32,355 --> 00:59:33,652
Come on, Percy. Hit me.

581
00:59:34,457 --> 00:59:35,321
I'm warning you.

582
00:59:35,525 --> 00:59:36,924
You warning me?

583
00:59:37,460 --> 00:59:38,358
I'm warning you!

584
00:59:38,562 --> 00:59:40,587
-You're warning me?!
-Shoot him!

585
00:59:40,797 --> 00:59:42,162
Well, come on--

586
00:59:48,738 --> 00:59:49,762
You're a big fucker.

587
00:59:51,007 --> 00:59:52,440
Where'd you come from?

588
01:00:03,053 --> 01:00:05,544
Come on, Dean.
Come on, boy, get up.

589
01:00:05,755 --> 01:00:07,313
All right. Let it breathe.

590
01:00:07,891 --> 01:00:09,984
That's it. Just breathe.
Just breathe.

591
01:00:11,861 --> 01:00:13,590
Breathe. Breathe, boy.

592
01:00:13,830 --> 01:00:16,799
-Didn't see it coming.
-Come on, boy, breathe.

593
01:00:17,000 --> 01:00:19,025
Come on. Just breathe.

594
01:00:21,871 --> 01:00:23,998
We thought he was doped.

595
01:00:25,275 --> 01:00:28,540
Didn't we? Didn't we, all of us,
think he was doped?

596
01:00:28,745 --> 01:00:30,474
You didn't ask?

597
01:00:31,781 --> 01:00:33,646
I guess that's not a mistake...

598
01:00:34,017 --> 01:00:37,248
...you'll be needing to make again
anytime soon, is it?

599
01:00:51,301 --> 01:00:54,930
You go get Dean and Harry looked at.
Make sure they're all right.

600
01:00:55,372 --> 01:00:58,899
Percy, you make the report
to the warden for me.

601
01:00:59,109 --> 01:01:01,669
Say the situation's under control.
It's not a story.

602
01:01:01,878 --> 01:01:04,540
He won't appreciate you
drawing out the suspense.

603
01:01:04,748 --> 01:01:06,978
What about you?
You're about to collapse.

604
01:01:07,217 --> 01:01:10,550
I've got the Mile
till you all come back.

605
01:01:11,321 --> 01:01:13,289
Go on now. Go.

606
01:01:20,964 --> 01:01:24,092
Come on, boy.
Let's get you looked at.

607
01:01:49,693 --> 01:01:53,129
Boss, I needs to see you down here.

608
01:01:56,666 --> 01:01:59,897
This is not a good time, John Coffey...

609
01:02:00,103 --> 01:02:02,071
...not a good time at all.

610
01:02:02,272 --> 01:02:06,402
But I needs to see you, boss.
I needs to talk to you.

611
01:02:28,465 --> 01:02:29,762
Closer.

612
01:02:30,300 --> 01:02:32,359
You know you ain't
supposed to do that.

613
01:02:34,003 --> 01:02:35,971
Mind your business, Del.

614
01:02:45,615 --> 01:02:47,640
What do you want, John Coffey?

615
01:02:48,718 --> 01:02:49,810
Just to help it.

616
01:02:53,490 --> 01:02:54,923
Don't be afraid.

617
01:02:55,492 --> 01:02:56,516
Help!

618
01:02:57,327 --> 01:02:58,191
Help!

619
01:02:58,395 --> 01:03:00,124
Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

620
01:03:00,330 --> 01:03:01,820
Help!

621
01:03:02,031 --> 01:03:03,123
What are you doing?

622
01:03:07,871 --> 01:03:09,702
Boss Howell! Help!

623
01:03:10,407 --> 01:03:12,136
Boss Stanton! Somebody, come!

624
01:03:30,860 --> 01:03:33,090
Help! Boss Howell! Boss Stanton!

625
01:03:33,296 --> 01:03:36,265
Somebody, come!
John Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

626
01:03:36,466 --> 01:03:39,094
Del, for chrissakes, shut up!

627
01:04:25,682 --> 01:04:27,912
What did you just do to me?

628
01:04:29,886 --> 01:04:31,581
I helped it.

629
01:04:32,655 --> 01:04:34,282
Didn't I help it?

630
01:04:35,391 --> 01:04:37,621
I just took it back, is all.

631
01:04:38,428 --> 01:04:40,896
Awful tired now, boss.

632
01:04:41,431 --> 01:04:43,126
Dog-tired.

633
01:05:07,257 --> 01:05:10,283
Boss, what that man do to you?

634
01:06:12,755 --> 01:06:15,519
Hey, honey. How you feeling?

635
01:06:17,327 --> 01:06:20,091
Oh, not too bad.

636
01:06:21,331 --> 01:06:23,094
What did the doctor say?

637
01:06:25,335 --> 01:06:27,064
You know doctors.

638
01:06:27,503 --> 01:06:29,403
Gobbledygook, mostly.

639
01:06:30,506 --> 01:06:31,871
Gobbledygook.

640
01:06:47,123 --> 01:06:48,715
Having stew tonight.

641
01:06:59,035 --> 01:07:00,730
What are you doing?

642
01:07:07,443 --> 01:07:09,308
What does it feel like?

643
01:07:10,179 --> 01:07:12,613
Well, I know what it feels like.

644
01:07:16,252 --> 01:07:18,152
It feels great.

645
01:07:54,924 --> 01:07:57,654
Not that I'm complaining...

646
01:07:58,795 --> 01:08:02,526
...but we haven't gone four times
in one night since we were 1 9.

647
01:08:02,765 --> 01:08:05,131
Yeah, we did, at your mom's.

648
01:08:06,636 --> 01:08:08,627
Wanna tell me what's going on?

649
01:08:12,442 --> 01:08:13,466
Well...

650
01:08:15,111 --> 01:08:17,102
...see, the thing is...

651
01:08:18,314 --> 01:08:21,875
...I never actually made it in
to Dr. Bishop's yesterday.

652
01:08:25,054 --> 01:08:27,852
Brutal, Paul. Listen.

653
01:08:28,057 --> 01:08:32,494
I'm thinking of taking the morning
off sick. You cover the fort for me?

654
01:08:33,563 --> 01:08:35,827
That's swell. Thanks.

655
01:08:36,032 --> 01:08:38,660
Yeah, I'm sure I'll feel better.

656
01:08:46,909 --> 01:08:48,877
You're sure you ought to do this?

657
01:08:50,480 --> 01:08:52,710
I'm not sure what I'm sure of.

658
01:09:09,532 --> 01:09:12,524
Burt, you got some company.

659
01:09:13,202 --> 01:09:14,794
Can I offer you a cold drink?

660
01:09:15,037 --> 01:09:18,131
Yes, ma'am. A cold drink
would be fine. Thank you.

661
01:09:18,474 --> 01:09:21,568
Mr. Hammersmith, your office said
I might find you at home.

662
01:09:21,778 --> 01:09:23,439
Hope I'm not troubling you.

663
01:09:24,113 --> 01:09:26,206
Well, that depends, Mr...?

664
01:09:26,415 --> 01:09:30,442
Paul Edgecomb. I'm E Block supervisor
up on Cold Mountain.

665
01:09:31,654 --> 01:09:33,019
The Green Mile.

666
01:09:33,222 --> 01:09:36,350
Yeah, I've heard of it.
Lost a few clients your way.

667
01:09:37,126 --> 01:09:38,855
I'd like to ask you about one.

668
01:09:40,997 --> 01:09:42,988
-Have a seat.
-Thank you.

669
01:09:47,737 --> 01:09:48,704
Which client?

670
01:09:50,973 --> 01:09:53,771
Now you got my curiosity aroused.

671
01:09:53,976 --> 01:09:55,307
John Coffey.

672
01:09:56,512 --> 01:09:57,638
Coffey.

673
01:09:58,114 --> 01:09:59,308
Causing you problems?

674
01:09:59,782 --> 01:10:03,343
Can't say he is. He doesn't like
the dark and cries on occasion...

675
01:10:03,553 --> 01:10:05,418
...but other than that....

676
01:10:05,588 --> 01:10:08,887
He cries, does he?
Got a lot to cry about, I'd say.

677
01:10:09,091 --> 01:10:10,649
You know what he did.

678
01:10:11,327 --> 01:10:13,352
I read the court transcript.

679
01:10:14,263 --> 01:10:15,093
Thank you, missus.

680
01:10:15,298 --> 01:10:17,027
My pleasure.

681
01:10:17,900 --> 01:10:18,730
IKids!

682
01:10:18,935 --> 01:10:21,199
Lunch is about ready.
Y'all come on up.

683
01:10:21,437 --> 01:10:22,734
Coming, Mama!

684
01:10:22,939 --> 01:10:26,067
What exactly are you
trying to find out?

685
01:10:26,676 --> 01:10:29,008
I wonder if he did anything
like that before.

686
01:10:30,479 --> 01:10:32,447
Why? Has he said anything?

687
01:10:32,648 --> 01:10:35,811
No, but a man who does
a thing like that...

688
01:10:36,018 --> 01:10:39,920
...has often developed a taste for it
over time. It occurred to me...

689
01:10:40,122 --> 01:10:44,024
...that it might be easy enough to
follow his back trail. Find out.

690
01:10:44,794 --> 01:10:48,594
A man his size, and colored to boot,
can't be that hard to trace.

691
01:10:48,798 --> 01:10:51,790
You'd think so, but you'd be wrong.

692
01:10:52,001 --> 01:10:54,128
Believe me, we tried.

693
01:10:54,971 --> 01:10:57,166
Like he'd dropped out of the sky.

694
01:10:57,974 --> 01:10:59,407
How can that be?

695
01:10:59,642 --> 01:11:03,840
We're in a depression.
A third of the country's out of work.

696
01:11:04,046 --> 01:11:08,073
People are drifting by the thousands,
looking for jobs, for greener grass.

697
01:11:08,317 --> 01:11:11,445
Even a giant like Coffey
wouldn't get noticed everywhere.

698
01:11:12,221 --> 01:11:14,553
Not until he kills
a couple of little girls.

699
01:11:15,391 --> 01:11:16,983
He is...

700
01:11:17,326 --> 01:11:19,385
...strange, I admit.

701
01:11:19,762 --> 01:11:24,062
But there doesn't seem to be
any real violence in him.

702
01:11:24,500 --> 01:11:26,934
I know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.

703
01:11:27,169 --> 01:11:30,002
I deal with them day in and day out.

704
01:11:30,806 --> 01:11:33,468
You didn't come to ask me
whether he killed before.

705
01:11:33,676 --> 01:11:36,611
You came to see if I think
he did it at all.

706
01:11:38,014 --> 01:11:38,912
Do you?

707
01:11:40,917 --> 01:11:43,078
One seldom sees a less ambiguous case.

708
01:11:43,286 --> 01:11:45,345
He was found with the victims
in his arms.

709
01:11:45,554 --> 01:11:47,351
And yet you defended him.

710
01:11:48,357 --> 01:11:50,951
Everyone is entitled to a defense.

711
01:11:51,360 --> 01:11:52,987
IKids! Lunch!

712
01:11:53,195 --> 01:11:54,492
Y'all listen to your mama!

713
01:11:59,135 --> 01:12:00,693
I'll tell you something.

714
01:12:01,771 --> 01:12:05,366
You listen close too, because it
might be something you need to know.

715
01:12:05,574 --> 01:12:06,939
I'm listening.

716
01:12:08,377 --> 01:12:09,435
We had us a dog.

717
01:12:10,479 --> 01:12:12,504
Just a sweet mongrel.

718
01:12:12,715 --> 01:12:14,205
You know the kind.

719
01:12:15,584 --> 01:12:19,020
Well, in many ways,
a good mongrel dog is like a Negro.

720
01:12:19,889 --> 01:12:21,652
You get to know it.

721
01:12:21,857 --> 01:12:26,226
Often, you get to love it.
It is of no particular use...

722
01:12:26,429 --> 01:12:29,956
...but you keep it around
because you think it loves you.

723
01:12:31,467 --> 01:12:35,597
If you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb, you
never have to find out any different.

724
01:12:36,672 --> 01:12:38,867
My wife and I were not so lucky.

725
01:12:40,843 --> 01:12:42,367
Caleb, come here for a second.

726
01:12:43,779 --> 01:12:44,973
Come here.

727
01:12:46,415 --> 01:12:47,677
Please, son.

728
01:12:49,285 --> 01:12:51,753
He still has the one good eye.

729
01:12:53,122 --> 01:12:55,386
I suppose he's lucky...

730
01:12:55,591 --> 01:12:57,957
...not to be completely blind.

731
01:13:00,663 --> 01:13:04,429
We get down on our knees and thank God
for that much at least.

732
01:13:05,101 --> 01:13:06,500
Right, Caleb?

733
01:13:09,338 --> 01:13:10,270
Go on in, now.

734
01:13:13,709 --> 01:13:16,644
That dog attacked my boy
for no reason.

735
01:13:17,246 --> 01:13:19,441
Just got it in his mind one day.

736
01:13:20,216 --> 01:13:21,683
The same with John Coffey.

737
01:13:21,884 --> 01:13:26,116
He was sorry afterwards.
Of that I have no doubt.

738
01:13:26,789 --> 01:13:28,654
But those little girls...

739
01:13:28,858 --> 01:13:31,292
...stayed raped and murdered.

740
01:13:31,961 --> 01:13:33,952
Maybe he'd never done it before.

741
01:13:35,731 --> 01:13:37,892
My dog never bit before.

742
01:13:39,635 --> 01:13:42,365
But I didn't concern myself with that.

743
01:13:43,372 --> 01:13:47,331
I went out with my rifle, grabbed
his collar and blew his brains out.

744
01:13:48,711 --> 01:13:49,871
Is Coffey guilty?

745
01:13:52,815 --> 01:13:54,544
Yes, he is.

746
01:13:55,151 --> 01:13:56,812
Don't you doubt it.

747
01:13:57,186 --> 01:13:59,654
And don't you turn your back on him.

748
01:14:00,489 --> 01:14:04,653
You may get away with it once
or even a hundred times...

749
01:14:05,494 --> 01:14:07,155
...but in the end...

750
01:14:09,165 --> 01:14:10,632
...you'll get bit.

751
01:14:23,212 --> 01:14:25,737
Oh, me! Oh, my!

752
01:14:32,588 --> 01:14:34,818
I'm smelling me some corn bread.

753
01:14:35,257 --> 01:14:37,157
It's from my missus.

754
01:14:40,863 --> 01:14:43,229
She wanted to thank you.

755
01:14:44,600 --> 01:14:45,999
Thank me for what?

756
01:14:46,435 --> 01:14:47,697
Well, you know.

757
01:14:50,439 --> 01:14:51,838
For helping me.

758
01:14:52,541 --> 01:14:54,099
Helping you with what?

759
01:14:54,810 --> 01:14:55,936
You know.

760
01:15:02,485 --> 01:15:04,453
Was your missus pleased?

761
01:15:06,288 --> 01:15:07,949
Several times.

762
01:15:23,472 --> 01:15:26,964
John, I can smell that from over here.
I surely can.

763
01:15:29,845 --> 01:15:32,143
Can I give Del and Mr. Jingles some?

764
01:15:32,748 --> 01:15:36,309
Well, it's yours, John.
You can do with it as you please.

765
01:15:39,355 --> 01:15:42,847
Here. This for Del and Mr. Jingles.

766
01:15:43,592 --> 01:15:47,255
Hey! What about me?
I'm gonna get some too, ain't I?

767
01:15:49,365 --> 01:15:52,493
It's yours, John. As you please.

768
01:15:53,102 --> 01:15:55,764
I think I'll just keep the rest, then.

769
01:16:01,610 --> 01:16:03,840
Courtesy of the gentleman
across the way.

770
01:16:06,081 --> 01:16:08,879
John, that's so very fine of you.

771
01:16:09,852 --> 01:16:13,754
I thank you. Mr. Jingle thank you.
My mama'd thank you too, but she dead.

772
01:16:14,390 --> 01:16:15,721
Welcome.

773
01:16:17,026 --> 01:16:21,156
What about me? Don't you
hold out on me, you big dummy nigger.

774
01:16:25,234 --> 01:16:26,701
Here come the boss man.

775
01:16:27,570 --> 01:16:30,038
You'll keep a civil tongue
on my block.

776
01:16:41,450 --> 01:16:43,475
You get that one for free.

777
01:16:44,486 --> 01:16:46,113
But that's the last one.

778
01:16:46,889 --> 01:16:49,824
That's it?
Just that little itty-bitty one?

779
01:16:50,392 --> 01:16:53,725
I guess I'm gonna have to
pay you out for the rest.

780
01:17:08,077 --> 01:17:09,066
Good shot, weren't it?

781
01:17:11,347 --> 01:17:13,474
