Percy, I got to ask you
a few questions.

1547
02:34:49,868 --> 02:34:53,133
One minute, he was fine,
and the next, blammo!

1548
02:34:53,372 --> 02:34:55,772
Dirty bastard grabbed him
through the bars.

1549
02:34:55,974 --> 02:34:58,204
Scared the boy so bad, he wet hisself.

1550
02:34:59,545 --> 02:35:02,446
See, we didn't even see it happen.

1551
02:35:06,385 --> 02:35:09,718
I'll cover for you as much as I can...

1552
02:35:09,922 --> 02:35:12,220
...even if it means my job.

1553
02:35:12,891 --> 02:35:14,722
But I have to know...

1554
02:35:15,127 --> 02:35:18,324
...does this have anything to do
with what happened at my house?

1555
02:35:21,233 --> 02:35:22,757
Does it, Paul?

1556
02:35:24,670 --> 02:35:25,932
No.

1557
02:36:53,358 --> 02:36:57,158
Does Hal know?
That Coffey's innocent, I mean.

1558
02:36:58,430 --> 02:37:00,159
Well, can he help?

1559
02:37:00,732 --> 02:37:03,530
Does he have the influence to do
something about this?

1560
02:37:03,735 --> 02:37:05,259
Stop the execution?

1561
02:37:05,504 --> 02:37:06,493
No.

1562
02:37:09,675 --> 02:37:11,165
Then don't tell him.

1563
02:37:11,843 --> 02:37:14,107
If it can't help, don't tell him.

1564
02:37:14,446 --> 02:37:15,708
Ever.

1565
02:37:18,050 --> 02:37:19,517
I won't.

1566
02:37:31,229 --> 02:37:33,595
There's no way out of this for you,
is there?

1567
02:37:35,067 --> 02:37:36,432
No.

1568
02:37:37,469 --> 02:37:40,029
And I've been thinking about it,
believe me.

1569
02:37:40,238 --> 02:37:43,571
I've been running it through my head
any number of ways.

1570
02:37:45,977 --> 02:37:48,104
I'll tell you the truth, honey.

1571
02:37:49,648 --> 02:37:54,483
I've done some things in my life
that I am not proud of...

1572
02:37:55,053 --> 02:37:59,922
...but this is the first time I've
ever felt real danger of hell.

1573
02:38:00,926 --> 02:38:02,291
Hell?

1574
02:38:08,166 --> 02:38:09,793
Talk to him.

1575
02:38:10,969 --> 02:38:12,800
Talk to John.

1576
02:38:14,573 --> 02:38:16,598
Find out what he wants.

1577
02:38:33,525 --> 02:38:34,753
Hello, boss.

1578
02:38:35,761 --> 02:38:37,092
Hello, John.

1579
02:38:38,530 --> 02:38:40,930
I guess you know we're
coming down to it now.

1580
02:38:41,700 --> 02:38:43,429
Another couple of days.

1581
02:38:56,982 --> 02:38:59,780
Is there anything special
you wanna eat that night?

1582
02:39:00,185 --> 02:39:02,483
We can rustle you up most anything.

1583
02:39:12,798 --> 02:39:17,462
Meat loaf be nice.
Mashed taters, gravy.

1584
02:39:17,736 --> 02:39:19,135
Okra.

1585
02:39:20,238 --> 02:39:23,071
Maybe some of that fine corn bread
your missus make...

1586
02:39:23,909 --> 02:39:25,968
...if she don't mind.

1587
02:39:28,280 --> 02:39:29,679
Now...

1588
02:39:30,215 --> 02:39:35,118
...what about a preacher?
Somebody to say a little prayer with.

1589
02:39:35,320 --> 02:39:37,481
Don't want no preacher.

1590
02:39:38,523 --> 02:39:41,048
You can say a prayer, if you like.

1591
02:39:41,693 --> 02:39:42,819
Me?

1592
02:39:45,831 --> 02:39:48,664
Suppose I could, if it came to that.

1593
02:39:56,875 --> 02:39:59,673
I have to ask you something
very important now.

1594
02:40:01,346 --> 02:40:03,541
I know what you gonna say.

1595
02:40:04,015 --> 02:40:05,505
You don't have to say it.

1596
02:40:05,851 --> 02:40:09,184
No, I do. I do.
I have to say it.

1597
02:40:13,124 --> 02:40:15,456
Tell me what you want me to do.

1598
02:40:16,361 --> 02:40:18,352
You want me to take you out of here?

1599
02:40:19,598 --> 02:40:23,591
Just let you run away?
See how far you could get?

1600
02:40:25,070 --> 02:40:27,766
Why would you do such a foolish thing?

1601
02:40:29,774 --> 02:40:31,901
On the day of my judgment...

1602
02:40:32,711 --> 02:40:34,906
...when I stand before God...

1603
02:40:35,113 --> 02:40:38,947
...and He asks me why did I...

1604
02:40:39,150 --> 02:40:41,778
...did I kill one of His true...

1605
02:40:42,654 --> 02:40:44,212
...miracles...

1606
02:40:45,390 --> 02:40:47,551
...what am I going to say?

1607
02:40:48,493 --> 02:40:50,222
That it was my job?

1608
02:40:52,397 --> 02:40:54,388
It's my job.

1609
02:40:54,699 --> 02:40:59,329
You tell God the Father
it was a kindness you done.

1610
02:41:02,474 --> 02:41:05,068
I know you're hurting and worrying.

1611
02:41:05,744 --> 02:41:09,407
I can feel it on you.
But you ought to quit on it now.

1612
02:41:10,582 --> 02:41:13,574
I want it to be over and done with.

1613
02:41:14,252 --> 02:41:15,742
I do.

1614
02:41:20,191 --> 02:41:22,182
I'm tired, boss.

1615
02:41:23,595 --> 02:41:27,964
Tired of being on the road,
lonely as a sparrow in the rain.

1616
02:41:29,167 --> 02:41:31,931
I'm tired of never having me
a buddy to be with...

1617
02:41:32,504 --> 02:41:37,100
...to tell me where we's going to,
coming from, or why.

1618
02:41:37,943 --> 02:41:42,175
Mostly, I'm tired of people
being ugly to each other.

1619
02:41:43,281 --> 02:41:47,240
I'm tired of all the pain
I feel and hear in the world...

1620
02:41:47,452 --> 02:41:49,113
...every day.

1621
02:41:49,487 --> 02:41:51,455
There's too much of it.

1622
02:41:51,790 --> 02:41:55,624
It's like pieces of glass
in my head...

1623
02:41:55,827 --> 02:41:58,125
...all the time.

1624
02:41:59,631 --> 02:42:01,690
Can you understand?

1625
02:42:04,636 --> 02:42:07,605
Yes, John, I think I can.

1626
02:42:09,975 --> 02:42:13,376
Well, there must be something
we can do for you, John.

1627
02:42:15,547 --> 02:42:17,572
There must be something that you want.

1628
02:42:26,992 --> 02:42:31,486
I ain't never seen me a flicker show.

1629
02:42:31,997 --> 02:42:34,124
Heaven

1630
02:42:34,332 --> 02:42:36,493
I'm in heaven

1631
02:42:37,402 --> 02:42:42,237
And my heart beats so
That I can hardly speak

1632
02:42:44,075 --> 02:42:48,910
And I seem to find
The happiness I seek

1633
02:42:50,515 --> 02:42:55,350
When we're out together
Dancing cheek to cheek

1634
02:43:57,415 --> 02:43:59,849
Why, they's angels.

1635
02:44:00,752 --> 02:44:03,414
Angels, just like up in heaven.

1636
02:45:04,082 --> 02:45:06,073
I'll be all right, fellas.

1637
02:45:07,485 --> 02:45:09,749
This here's the hard part.

1638
02:45:11,055 --> 02:45:12,579
I'll be all right in a while.

1639
02:45:15,393 --> 02:45:18,260
I should have this just for now.

1640
02:45:22,267 --> 02:45:24,701
I'll give it back after.

1641
02:45:27,772 --> 02:45:32,368
You know, I fell asleep this afternoon
and had me a dream.

1642
02:45:33,578 --> 02:45:35,671
I dreamed about Del's mouse.

1643
02:45:36,848 --> 02:45:38,076
Did you, John?

1644
02:45:38,850 --> 02:45:43,253
I dreamed Mr. Jingles got down to
that place Boss Howell talked about.

1645
02:45:43,454 --> 02:45:45,752
That Mouseville place.

1646
02:45:46,024 --> 02:45:48,356
I dreamed there's kids.

1647
02:45:48,927 --> 02:45:52,363
And how they laughed
at his tricks. My!

1648
02:45:54,866 --> 02:45:58,666
I dreamed that those two little
blonde-headed girls was there.

1649
02:45:58,870 --> 02:46:00,735
They's laughing too.

1650
02:46:00,939 --> 02:46:03,874
I put my arms around them
and set them on my knees.

1651
02:46:04,075 --> 02:46:08,136
And they was no blood coming out
of they hair, and they's just fine.

1652
02:46:08,379 --> 02:46:11,712
We all watched Mr. Jingles
roll that spool.

1653
02:46:13,218 --> 02:46:16,654
How we did laugh.
Fit to bust, we was!

1654
02:46:34,906 --> 02:46:38,967
They's lots of folks here
that hate me. Lots!

1655
02:46:40,912 --> 02:46:42,971
I can feel it.

1656
02:46:43,181 --> 02:46:44,910
It's like bees stinging me.

1657
02:46:45,250 --> 02:46:47,616
Well, feel how we feel, then.

1658
02:46:48,920 --> 02:46:50,080
We don't hate you.

1659
02:46:51,522 --> 02:46:53,080
Can you feel that?

1660
02:46:55,326 --> 02:46:57,487
IKill him twice, you boys!

1661
02:46:58,263 --> 02:47:02,256
You go on and kill that raping
babykiller twice!

1662
02:47:02,467 --> 02:47:04,298
That'd be fine!

1663
02:47:20,985 --> 02:47:23,453
Wipe your face before
you stand up, Dean.

1664
02:47:23,655 --> 02:47:24,952
Yes, sir.

1665
02:47:37,235 --> 02:47:38,293
Roll on one.

1666
02:47:46,311 --> 02:47:49,838
Does it hurt yet? I hope it does.

1667
02:47:50,648 --> 02:47:52,912
I hope it hurts like hell.

1668
02:47:54,886 --> 02:47:57,446
John Coffey, you've been condemned
to die in the electric chair...

1669
02:47:57,655 --> 02:47:58,917
...by a jury of your peers.

1670
02:47:59,157 --> 02:48:02,558
Sentence imposed by a judge
in good standing in this state.

1671
02:48:03,027 --> 02:48:06,258
Do you have anything to say
before sentence is carried out?

1672
02:48:07,999 --> 02:48:10,524
I'm sorry for what I am.

1673
02:48:22,547 --> 02:48:24,276
Please, boss...

1674
02:48:25,683 --> 02:48:28,379
...don't put that thing over my face.

1675
02:48:29,587 --> 02:48:31,919
Don't put me in the dark.

1676
02:48:32,690 --> 02:48:35,022
I's afraid of the dark.

1677
02:48:44,702 --> 02:48:46,363
All right, John.

1678
02:49:06,557 --> 02:49:09,583
Heaven, I'm in heaven

1679
02:49:09,794 --> 02:49:12,627
Heaven, heaven

1680
02:49:12,830 --> 02:49:14,661
I'm in heaven

1681
02:49:15,233 --> 02:49:17,827
Heaven, heaven

1682
02:49:18,069 --> 02:49:19,764
I'm in heaven

1683
02:49:40,691 --> 02:49:42,283
John Coffey...

1684
02:49:43,327 --> 02:49:46,455
...electricity shall pass through
your body until you are dead...

1685
02:49:46,664 --> 02:49:48,825
...in accordance with state law.

1686
02:49:51,202 --> 02:49:54,933
May God have mercy on your soul.

1687
02:50:33,644 --> 02:50:35,578
You have to say it.

1688
02:50:37,248 --> 02:50:39,546
You have to give the order.

1689
02:50:57,568 --> 02:50:59,866
He killed them with they love.

1690
02:51:00,071 --> 02:51:04,906
That's how it is every day
all over the world.

1691
02:51:18,689 --> 02:51:20,122
Roll on two.

1692
02:53:04,795 --> 02:53:08,162
It was the last execution
I ever took part in.

1693
02:53:08,466 --> 02:53:12,197
I just couldn't do it anymore
after that. Brutal either.

1694
02:53:13,371 --> 02:53:18,070
We both transferred out,
took jobs with Boys' Correctional.

1695
02:53:18,309 --> 02:53:20,072
It was all right.

1696
02:53:20,711 --> 02:53:23,646
''Catch them young'' became my motto.

1697
02:53:26,884 --> 02:53:28,010
You don't believe me.

1698
02:53:28,886 --> 02:53:31,411
I don't imagine you'd lie to me, Paul.

1699
02:53:32,223 --> 02:53:34,384
-It's just that--
-It's quite a story.

1700
02:53:34,592 --> 02:53:36,822
It's quite a story.

1701
02:53:37,228 --> 02:53:39,594
One thing I don't understand.

1702
02:53:39,830 --> 02:53:41,593
You said you and Jan...

1703
02:53:41,832 --> 02:53:45,393
...had a grown son in 1 935.

1704
02:53:45,670 --> 02:53:47,160
Is that right?

1705
02:53:47,538 --> 02:53:49,506
The math doesn't work, does it?

1706
02:53:55,179 --> 02:53:57,773
Do you feel up to taking a walk?

1707
02:54:18,436 --> 02:54:19,869
Watch your step.

1708
02:54:20,371 --> 02:54:22,703
Now let your eyes adjust.

1709
02:54:34,552 --> 02:54:35,576
There.

1710
02:54:39,390 --> 02:54:41,119
Wake up, old fella.

1711
02:54:41,392 --> 02:54:42,654
Wake up.

1712
02:54:46,230 --> 02:54:50,098
Paul, it isn't. It can't be.

1713
02:54:54,305 --> 02:54:55,636
Come over here, boy.

1714
02:54:56,140 --> 02:54:58,506
Come on over here and see this lady.

1715
02:55:01,412 --> 02:55:04,438
That can't be Mr. Jingles.

1716
02:55:27,104 --> 02:55:29,698
Go on, you can do it.

1717
02:55:36,781 --> 02:55:41,275
This isn't exactly the Mouseville
we had in mind, is it?

1718
02:55:42,052 --> 02:55:46,011
But we make do. Don't we, old fella?

1719
02:55:52,463 --> 02:55:56,126
I think Mr. Jingles
happened by accident.

1720
02:55:56,567 --> 02:56:01,436
I think when we electrocuted Del,
and it all went so badly...

1721
02:56:01,639 --> 02:56:04,039
...well, John could feel that,
you know.

1722
02:56:04,241 --> 02:56:07,642
And I think a part of...

1723
02:56:07,878 --> 02:56:10,540
...whatever magic was inside of him...

1724
02:56:10,815 --> 02:56:14,148
...just leapt into my tiny friend here.

1725
02:56:15,319 --> 02:56:17,310
As for me...

1726
02:56:18,489 --> 02:56:21,049
...John had to give me
a part of himself...

1727
02:56:21,325 --> 02:56:23,486
...a gift, the way he saw it...

1728
02:56:23,828 --> 02:56:27,264
...so that I could see for myself
what Wild Bill had done.

1729
02:56:29,667 --> 02:56:31,897
When John did that...

1730
02:56:33,337 --> 02:56:35,669
...when he took my hand...

1731
02:56:36,674 --> 02:56:40,576
...a part of the power
that worked through him...

1732
02:56:41,512 --> 02:56:43,377
...spilled into me.

1733
02:56:43,747 --> 02:56:45,578
He...what?

1734
02:56:46,016 --> 02:56:49,543
He infected you with life?

1735
02:56:51,121 --> 02:56:53,453
It's as good a word as any.

1736
02:56:54,959 --> 02:56:57,860
He infected us both,
didn't he, Mr. Jingles?

1737
02:56:58,062 --> 02:56:59,529
With life.

1738
02:57:03,601 --> 02:57:06,695
I'm 1 08 years old, Elaine.

1739
02:57:06,937 --> 02:57:11,306
I was 44 the year that John Coffey
walked the Green Mile.

1740
02:57:14,211 --> 02:57:17,977
You mustn't blame John.
He couldn't help what happened.

1741
02:57:18,215 --> 02:57:22,777
He was just a force of nature.

1742
02:57:23,220 --> 02:57:27,418
I've lived to see
some amazing things, Ellie.

1743
02:57:28,459 --> 02:57:31,428
Another century come to pass.

1744
02:57:34,164 --> 02:57:38,624
But I've had to see my friends and
loved ones die off through the years.

1745
02:57:39,003 --> 02:57:41,062
Hal and Melinda...

1746
02:57:41,505 --> 02:57:42,938
...Brutus Howell...

1747
02:57:43,140 --> 02:57:45,802
...my wife, my boy.

1748
02:57:48,746 --> 02:57:50,611
And you, Elaine.

1749
02:57:51,615 --> 02:57:53,412
You'll die too.

1750
02:57:54,919 --> 02:57:59,322
And my curse is knowing
that I'll be there to see it.

1751
02:58:00,758 --> 02:58:03,192
It's my atonement, you see.

1752
02:58:03,761 --> 02:58:05,490
It's my punishment...

1753
02:58:05,696 --> 02:58:08,324
...for letting John Coffey
ride the lightning.

1754
02:58:10,034 --> 02:58:12,798
For killing a miracle of God.

1755
02:58:14,338 --> 02:58:17,102
Almighty, everlasting God...

1756
02:58:17,408 --> 02:58:19,808
...the source of all being and life.

1757
02:58:20,010 --> 02:58:24,344
You'll be gone like all the others.
I'll have to stay.

1758
02:58:26,350 --> 02:58:30,548
I'll die eventually.
Of that I'm sure.

1759
02:58:31,288 --> 02:58:35,281
I have no illusions of immortality.

1760
02:58:35,659 --> 02:58:38,150
But I will have wished for death...

1761
02:58:38,862 --> 02:58:41,057
...long before death finds me.

1762
02:58:42,166 --> 02:58:46,000
In truth, I wish for it already.

1763
02:58:58,082 --> 02:59:00,073
Mr. Jingles?

1764
02:59:09,059 --> 02:59:11,220
Where you been?

1765
02:59:11,662 --> 02:59:14,927
Been worried about you, boy.
You hungry?

1766
02:59:15,766 --> 02:59:18,200
Let's see if we can find you
something to eat.

1767
02:59:19,336 --> 02:59:23,067
A few crumbs anyway.
I know you'd like that.

1768
02:59:24,508 --> 02:59:25,839
Look at you.

1769
02:59:27,544 --> 02:59:31,446
I lie in bed most nights
thinking about it.

1770
02:59:31,649 --> 02:59:33,674
And I wait.

1771
02:59:34,585 --> 02:59:37,315
I think about all the people
I've loved...

1772
02:59:37,521 --> 02:59:39,682
...now long gone.

1773
02:59:40,424 --> 02:59:42,858
I think about my beautiful Jan...

1774
02:59:43,060 --> 02:59:46,086
...how I lost her so many years ago.

1775
02:59:47,464 --> 02:59:52,094
And I think about all of us walking
our own Green Mile...

1776
02:59:52,302 --> 02:59:54,964
...each in our own time.

1777
02:59:56,040 --> 02:59:59,237
But one thought
more than any other...

1778
02:59:59,443 --> 03:00:02,071
...keeps me awake most nights:

1779
03:00:03,247 --> 03:00:07,206
If he could make a mouse
live so long...

1780
03:00:07,718 --> 03:00:10,778
...how much longer do I have?

1781
03:00:14,091 --> 03:00:16,855
We each owe a death.

1782
03:00:17,061 --> 03:00:19,552
There are no exceptions.

1783
03:00:20,330 --> 03:00:22,321
But, oh, God...

1784
03:00:23,233 --> 03:00:25,030
...sometimes...

1785
03:00:25,636 --> 03:00:29,231
...the Green Mile seems so long.

